{"body": "I think the main reason that @tenderlove want to do this is to lower the number of thread current variables and this current implementation is not changing anything.\r\n\r\nI may be wrong but I think we have to do something like this:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclass ScopeRegistry\r\n  def self.current\r\n    Thread.current[\"scope_registry\"] ||= new\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def initialize\r\n    @current_scopes = {}\r\n    @ignore_default_scopes = {}\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def current_scope_for(class_name)\r\n    @current_scopes[class_name]\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  def set_current_scope_for(class_name, value)\r\n    @current_scopes[class_name] = value\r\n  end\r\n\r\n  ...\r\n```", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/16055417", "created_at": "2013-04-08T14:59:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10135#issuecomment-16055417", "updated_at": "2013-04-08T14:59:58Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 10135, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rafaelfranca", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2c7b84fa30f0cea96a90729afe2970a0.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/received_events", "gravatar_id": "0525b332aafb83307b32d9747a93de03", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rafaelfranca", "type": "User", "id": 47848, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rafaelfranca/followers"}